Warning: As this doesn't appear to be a bug with Tensorflow, the devs may ask for this to be moved to Stack Overflow.

This is because when you have trained with your dataset you are retraining the final output layers with new classes (traffic signs). This will not retain the imagenet results. This is a question for S/O.

If you decide to move this issue to Stack Overflow, please post the link here so that myself (or others that stumble upon this issue) can find the S/O thread.

_Warning: As this doesn't appear to be a bug with Tensorflow, the devs may ask for this to be moved to Stack Overflow._

This is because when you have trained with your dataset you are retraining the final output layers with new classes (traffic signs). This will not retain the imagenet results. This is a question for S/O.

If you decide to move this issue to Stack Overflow, please post the link here so that myself (or others that stumble upon this issue) can find the S/O thread.
